# Internal compliance documents — contain specifics of auth/security controls
# that shouldn't be advertised publicly. File lives at docs/compliance_audit.md
# locally so README link works and future audits can diff against it.
docs/compliance_audit.md
docs/compliance_audit_*.md

# Local debug dumps — never commit (contains real mailbox data)
probe.json
*.probe.json

# Compliance audits (sensitive — paths + gaps named)
audit/

# Private punch list (internal file paths, audit gaps, infra
# hostnames — not for public repo exposure). Source of truth for
# tracked items, managed locally.
PUNCH-LIST.md
PUNCH-LIST-COMPLETED.md

# Internal Gmail Pub/Sub setup runbook — contains GCP project IDs,
# service-account emails, Tailscale hostnames, and homelab-specific
# infra details that shouldn't be advertised publicly. Operator-
# private companion to the public README "Set up Gmail push" section.
docs/gmail-pubsub-setup.md

# Session-recovery snapshots — capture deploy state, queued work,
# and infra IDs in case the project context is corrupted between
# sessions. Same privacy posture as the operator runbook.
docs/session-recovery*.md

# Operator-private backup/restore runbook. Spells out the recommended
# split-storage pattern + verbatim CLI commands; not appropriate for
# the public README which keeps the description scoped to "the feature
# exists; here's where the button is."
docs/backup-restore.md

# Operator-private QA handover doc — brings a fresh QA agent (Cowork
# workspace, contractor, etc.) up to speed. Names internal infra +
# admin URL paths + persona-matrix specifics that don't belong in the
# public repo.
docs/cowork-qa-handover.md

# Operator-private OpenClaw-skill handover doc. Combined from the
# previously-tracked handover files in openclaw/skills/email-triage-api/
# (#90, 2026-04-30): contains gateway hostname + token alias names +
# internal infra paths that don't belong in the public repo.
docs/openclaw-skill-handover.md


# Operator-private deploy-script env (DEPLOYHOST / AGENTHOST /
# NAGIOS_HOST). Operator copies scripts/deploy.env.local.example
# -> deploy.env.local and fills in their hostnames; the .example
# stays committed with neutral placeholders.
scripts/deploy.env.local
.coverage

# Operator-private publish-workflow runbook. Documents the contract
# with feedback_strict_action_gating.md (Tier-3 publish verb), names
# internal remote conventions, and lists recovery procedures that
# reference operator-private infra. The script + pattern catalogue
# (scripts/publish-public-mirror.sh + scripts/publish-scrub-patterns.txt)
# stay tracked.
docs/PUBLISH-WORKFLOW.md

# Operator-private M-series HIPAA exposure audit. Names internal
# source-line citations + the Phase-3/4 lift mechanisms; companion to
# the public docs/privacy-audit-runbook.md which keeps the description
# scoped to the user-facing invariants.
docs/m-series-hipaa-audit.md
